)FUNCTION
     KMBAPFLB IS A BATCH PROGRAM THAT WILL ADD OR REMOVE A LOAD
     LIBRARY, TO, OR FROM, THE APF LIST.

     THIS PROGRAM WILL ADD A DATASET TO THE APF LIST
     THAT IS POINTED TO BY THE APFLIB DDNAME

)SYNTAX      THIS IS A BATCH PROGRAM, AND HERE IS SAMPLE JCL:

         //SBGOLOBK  JOB (ACCT#),S-GOLOB,
         // NOTIFY=&SYSUID,
         // CLASS=B,MSGCLASS=X
         //*
         //ADDAPF  EXEC PGM=KMBAPFLB
         //*REMAPF EXEC PGM=KMBAPFLB,PARM='REMOVE'
         //STEPLIB DD DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.W$$.LINKLIB  (authorized)
         //APFLIB  DD DISP=SHR,DSN=SBGOLOB.LOAD

 --------------------------------------------------------------------
         ADDED DYNAMIC APF SUPPORT

  KBASS1 04/04/2011 ADDED 'REMOVE' PARAMETER TO REMOVE AN APF LIBRARY
     //SB1      EXEC PGM=KMBAPFLB,PARM='REMOVE'
